            <h2>1. Information Collection and Use Cases</h2>
            <p>We collect selective information so that we can provide an experience that is responsive to our users&rsquo; and customers&rsquo; needs. If requested by the Testing Institution, our Services will utilize an image and audio detection feature to help determine if the image or audio of a person is visible or can be heard, or if one or more individual is visible or can be heard by the device&rsquo;s camera and microphone (without trying to identify any person by using an ID with personal information, driver&rsquo;s license, room scan, or password). We use this feature solely to provide our Services to the Testing Institution and we securely encrypt the storage of images and audio, or individualized data related to image or audio detection for 12-month periods of time, as directed by your Testing Institution, unless the Institution requires an exception to our time period of storage, or we need to retain the data to uphold our commitment to the Institution, which may not exceed two (2) years after your last instance of utilizing our Services, at which time all student data is automatically extracted and disposed.</p>
            <p>If requested by the Testing Institution, our Services may record your activity upon launching or during the assessment, by capturing audio and/or visual recordings from your device via microphone and/or camera, or from an external microphone or camera (for these purposes, we request that you grant us permission to use your browser and device). Please note that these recordings may also capture images or audio of other people who are in or around your surrounding workspace area. If you are using our Services at your home or in a personal space, you agree to allow your activity and surrounding workspace area to be recorded by camera and microphone and then to be viewed by your instructor, administrator, or qualified MCID staff members before, during, or after the assessment as directed by your Testing Institution for the purpose of detecting any indication of cheating on the assessment. Based on the specific requirements of your Testing Institution and the Services engaged, you may be asked to submit certain information about yourself, in which you authorize us to gather your contact information (that may include your name, address, telephone number, email address, student or other ID#). This information may be used for customer support or submitting payment.</p>
