            <p>We collect this information to improve our service or Product &amp; Platform, and to help us determine your individual needs so we may serve you better individually, as well as collectively. Please note, to better safeguard your information, please do not include any credit card information in your electronic communication unless it is specifically required as part of services or transaction fulfillment process site, or our customer service contact process.</p>

            <h2>2. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We utilize the highest level of AWS S3 security with 256k encryption to protect the storage of data, and the connection and transmission of information during the assessment. Our level of security also ensures protection against the loss, misuse, alteration and disruption of the information under our control. All data is selectively placed in an encrypted and dedicated, private Amazon cloud platform within US based and regionally secure data centers. Only select and fully qualified MCID staff are entitled access to ensure college faculty and administrators are supported on behalf of their students to uphold the academic integrity as contracted by their institution. Each of the qualified MCID staff members entitled to access are committed to executing on behalf of the Family Education and Privacy Act (FERPA) requirements. We may also at times provide information about you to third parties who deliver various services on our behalf, such as providers who process credit card payments. We will only share information about you that is necessary for the third party to deliver the requested service. These companies are prohibited from retaining, sharing, buying, selling, storing or using your personally identifiable information for any secondary purposes. We follow generally accepted standards to protect the personal information submitted to us, both during transmission and once we receive it.</p>

